The absence hours are managed by Business Central as "classic" hours: it is necessary to create a specific internal job.  

The job must have the following characteristics: 

* The customer must coincide with the company name of the company itself. Usually, it is used the customer created for the self-invoice. 

* As responsible person it is included the HR resource who deals with the management and control of absences.  

* The job type is internal (the order type has the “internal work” flag active):

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000817-0/setup eng1.png"><br>

The WBS structure of the absences job lists all possible causes of absence. The billing type is “no billing”:

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000817-0/setup eng2.png"><br>